claim.claim-text:
37. A method for visually monitoring a chemical substance, comprising: 
disposing the chemical substance in a vessel that includes a base portion, a wall portion extending away from the base portion and having at least one transparent region, and an interface region at an interface between the wall portion and the base portion; 
positioning the chemical substance at least proximate to a background material fixedly attached to the vessel with the background material covering at least part of the base portion and/or at least part of the interface region; 
moving the vessel and the background material as a unit; and 
viewing the chemical substance and the background material simultaneously through the at least one transparent region of the wall portion.

46. The method of claim 37, further comprising: 
disposing a chemical indicator in the vessel; 
disposing a titrating substance in the vessel; 
stirring the contents of the vessel; and 
detecting an equivalence point of the contents of the vessel by viewing the chemical substance through the vessel wall while the chemical substance is positioned adjacent to the background material and determining an amount of the titrating substance added to the vessel when the contents of the vessel changes from a first color to a second color.

49. A method for visually monitoring a chemical substance, comprising: 
disposing the chemical substance in a vessel having a base portion, a wall portion extending away from the base portion and having at least one transparent region, and an interface region at an interface between the wall portion and the base portion; 
positioning the chemical substance at least proximate to a background material fixedly attached to the vessel with the background material covering at least part of the base portion, and/or at least part of the interface region, the background material having a first region with a first hue and a second region with a second hue different than the first hue; 
moving the vessel and the background material as a unit; and 
viewing the chemical substance and the background material simultaneously through the at least one transparent portion of the wall portion while the chemical substance is positioned adjacent to the first and second regions of the background material.

54. A method for titrating a liquid chemical substance, comprising: 
disposing the liquid chemical substance and an indicator in a vessel having a base portion and a generally transparent wall portion extending away from the base portion; 
positioning the liquid chemical substance adjacent to an opaque background material fixedly attached to the base portion with the opaque background material covering at least approximately the entire base portion; 
moving the vessel and the background material as a unit and without moving the background material relative to the vessel; 
disposing a titrating agent in the vessel; 
stirring the contents of the vessel; and 
detecting an equivalence point of the contents of the vessel by viewing the chemical substance through the wall portion while the chemical substance is positioned adjacent to the opaque background material and determining an amount of the titrating agent added to the vessel when the contents of the vessel changes from a first color to a second color different than the first color.
